The Japanese term '''Madogiwazoku''' refers to a form of [[constructive dismissal]].  It translates as '''the window-gazing tribe'''[http://www.apmforum.com/japan/hrm-art4.htm].  In the West it is often colloquially known as being given a '''window job'''[http://everything2.com/index.pl?node_id=1317016].   The undesirable employee is transfered into an office with a desk and a chair and given nothing to do except stare out the window all day, until he finally gets the message and resigns.[http://www.daijob.com/dj4/en/column/terrie/column.jsp?id=717]